h1. {anchor:context}Context
Ista operates servers in two environments: - *Azure* — organized in landing zones, each with an operationally responsible team \("owner") - *On-premises* — hosted at OEDIV and 3S

*Two types of Azure landing zones:*

|| Type || Description || Managed by ||
| Self-managed | Operated DevOps-style by the owning squad | The squad itself |
| Centrally-managed | Operated by a central admin team | LOT Server Infrastructure \(SI), Network Infrastructure \(NI), or Database Infrastructure \(DI) |

Most centrally managed landing zones belong to country operations; some are application-specific. Country landing zones often host multiple applications.

*LeanIX* is used as the Enterprise Architecture Repository. It tracks business applications and IT components — but not servers.

----
h1. {anchor:problem}Problem
Multiple teams need to know, for each server: - Which team is operationally responsible for it? \(e.g. for immediate security fixes) - Which team is accountable for the servers regarding compliance and costs? - Which application is running on it? - Is it a production server?

----
h1. {anchor:systems-requiring-server-tags}Systems requiring server tags
* *EDR* - SoC needs to react on security event. Needs metadata for assessing situation and contacting stakeholders.
* *Tenable* - Basis for 10GR reporting of vulnerabilities. Application owners need to see their affected servers.
* *Grafana* - TODO explain use case
* *PowerBI FinOps report* - Needs to know who leads the team accountable for a server to inform them about cloud costs.
* *10GR report* - PowerBI report for all 10 golden rules KPIs.

h1. {anchor:required-server-tags}Required Server Tags
Server tags are going to be maintained and/or consolidated in the CMDB \(IFS Assyst). From there this information can be synced to other tools which need server tags.

|| Tag || Allowed Values || Used by ||
| *Application* | Registered LeanIX applications | EDR, Tenable, Grafana |
| *Operationally Responsible Team* \(maintaining team) | Registered LeanIX team. LeanIX has team placeholders for local IT of countries | EDR |
| *Accountable Team* | Registered LeanIX team. LeanIX has team placeholders for local IT of countries | Tenable |
| *IT Component* | Registered LeanIX IT Components | EDR, Tenable, Grafana _\(data quality improvement planned for 2027)_ |
| *Server Type* | prod, nonprod | EDR, Tenable |
| *10GR group* | LeanIX Tribe or local IT Team | 10GR report, Tenable \(\+ all other systems delivering 10GR data) |

bq. Names in LeanIX can change. It is important that the CMDB stores the LeanIX factsheet IDs internally as canonical identifiers to be able to update the tag values.
----
h1. {anchor:azure-servers}Azure Servers
The process for the initial filling and the continuous update for Azure servers is the same. LeanIX data should just be imported / refreshed in regular intervals.

*Application Tag* For each server: - Look up the landing zone factsheet in LeanIX with the Azure subscription ID associated to the server - Read the relation "Hosted Applications" in LeanIX - If only one application: use application name - If multiple applications or empty: use "accountable team" > name

bq. In the case of country subscriptions, the accountable team will be "local IT _\(COUNTRY)_".
*Operationally Responsible Team Tag* - Look up the landing zone and take the team from the relation "operationally responsible Org Structure"

*Accountable Team Tag* - Look up the landing zone and take the team from the relation "accountable Org Structure"

*Server Type Tag \(prod / nonprod)* - Check the LeanIX factsheet if the subscription id is in the "PROD subscription ID" field or on the "NONPROD subscription ID" field and set accordingly.

*10GR group* - Lookup the landing zone and take the "accountable Org Structure": If it’s a "local IT" team, use the name. If it’s another team, navigate to the parent \(tribe) and take the tribe name.

h1. {anchor:on-premises-servers-oediv-3s}On-premises Servers \(OEDIV, 3S)
h2. {anchor:initial-data-fill}Initial Data Fill
*Application Tag*

* Tunde’s \(IT Security) existing on-prem tag evaluation is used as the starting point.
* LOT SI, DI, and NI verify correctness and plausibility.

*Operationally Responsible Team Tag* - Value is either SI, NI, or DI. LOTs align on responsibilities between themselves.

*Accountable Team Tag* - LOT SI pre-fills based on best knowledge; LOT SI, NI, and DI align on responsibilities between themselves.

*Server Type Tag \(prod / nonprod)* - All on-premises servers default to *nonprod*. - Application owners are asked to update the classification for production environments. - Nonprod classification allows SoC to act quickly \(e.g. shutdown) if needed. - Application owners have an incentive to update the classification, because nonprod servers can be shutdown at any time.

*10GR group* - Accountable Tribe or Country filled by LOTs based on best knowledge.

bq. Note\! This is a new tag\! The definition has impact on the current work for the initial data fill.
h2. {anchor:keeping-tag-data-up-to-date}Keeping Tag Data Up-to-Date
|| Trigger || Process ||
| New server or configuration change | LOT SI \(or NI/DI) updates server tag information directly in IFSassyst |

h1. {anchor:ongoing-quality-monitoring}Ongoing Quality Monitoring
* The PowerBI report will be extended to show missing tags.
* ITAM Squad reviews tag consistency at least monthly and triggers corrective actions \(approaching LOTs or App Owners as needed).

h1. {anchor:api-and-data-delivery}API and Data Delivery
IFSassyst will expose the following server data via API and/or file export to EDR and Tenable:

* Server name
* LeanIX Application
* LeanIX IT Component
* Operationally Responsible Team
* Accountable Team
* Server Type \(Prod / Non-Prod)
* 10GR group \(Tribe or Country)

*Security concern:* A compromise of IFSassyst could lead to mass tag changes, which would cause incorrect permissions in EDR and other tools.

Proposed mitigations: - IFSassyst is monitored by SIEM with a focus on detecting mass changes - Data exchange via regular export/import \(with a partial human review step) rather than direct live API - IFSassyst frontend changes require ITAM Squad approval to limit human error

h1. {anchor:access-control-rbac}Access Control \(RBAC)
Viewing server and tag data for all servers is restricted to: - IT Security and SoC - IT Infrastructure LOTs - We enable IT Asset Management \(Patrick) - We drive Public Cloud Adoption \(Janusz) - We enable Public Cloud Solutions \(Jan)

All other teams and application owners have limited, scoped access only \(where technically possible).

